The paper discusses a service for managing high-throughput task scheduling and execution on supercomputing systems, which involves distributed computing, machine learning, and software engineering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the automation of scheduling and execution, which falls under the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also mentions load balancing and fault tolerance, which are topics in cs.Distributed Systems. Finally, the paper discusses the use of provenance data, which is relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
